twilightforest.book.icetower.1.description:
§8[[An explorer's notebook, caked in ice]]§0

I overcame one blizzard, only to run into this terrible ice storm atop the glacier. My explorations have shown me the splendor of an ice palace, shining with the colors of the

twilightforest.book.icetower.3.description:
leader of the minotaurs nearby.

Surrounding this glacier, there are masses of yetis. Perhaps the yetis have some sort of leader...

twilightforest.book.icetower.2.description:

§5§nCONTAINERS§0§r

§5§nOFFHAND PRIORITY§0§r
Having blocks in your offhand will place them instead of the block you're looking at.

book.extendedcrafting.entry.compression..description: Quantum Compression is the process of compressing items a little too much. This is done using a Quantum Compressor. $(br2)The Quantum Compressor is a powered machine that can hold and compress extremely large amounts of materials. Items placed inside the Quantum Compressor go into an internal buffer for use in compression. The buffer is represented as a blue bar.

create.ponder.item_vault_storage.text_1.description: Item Vaults can be used to store large amounts of items

book.extendedcrafting.entry.compression..description: Each recipe $(bold)usually$() requires a catalyst. The catalyst is placed in the left-most slot and does not get used up. $(br2)Once there are enough items in the buffer, the machine will begin to craft the item. The Quantum Compressor will only use power while crafting. $(br2)If you happen to put items into the compressor that you would rather not lose forever, you can press the eject button above the input slot to get them back.

Items in the buffer are stored in the endless void and can only be re-obtained by ejecting. Breaking the block will cause those items to get lost forever, so be careful! $(br2)The item input buffer of the Quantum Compressor is capable of holding $(bold)billions$() of items, but by default will only hold as many as the recipe requires. You can disable this limit by clicking on the lock button next to the input buffer.

tombstone.compendium.alignment.desc.description:
The alignment depends on the actions performed by the player.
Alignment increases:
- by using a soul receptacle on a grave to free the soul
- by killing pillagers and zombies during a village siege
- by exorcising a zombie-villager with the Ankh prayer
- by protecting a villager with the Ankh prayer
Alignment decreases:
- by killing villagers
- by using a tablet of cupidity
- by plundering an abandoned player grave without the key
The citizens and raiders of Minecolonies are considered to be villagers and pillagers, respectively.
It can unlock some perks or allow to use some magical items.
Each level of alignment also reduces the damage done by undead / living creatures depending on your side of alignment.
The damage reduction does not affect those of others players.

text.autoconfig.fallingtree.option.tools.description:
Applies a speed modifier when breaking the tree.

0 will disable this, so the speed will be the default one of breaking a block.
If set to 1 each log block will be counted once, so if the tree is 5 blocks tall it'll require the time of breaking 5 logs.
If set to 2 each log block will be counted twice, so if the tree is 5 blocks tall, it'll require the time of breaking 10 logs.

INFO: Only in INSTANTANEOUS mode.
WARNING: If you are on a server, this either has to be set to 0 or every player should have the mod. Else they'll have a weird effect of breaking the block but the block is still there.

tombstone.compendium.prayer.desc.description:
The Ankh allows you to use prayers by period.
You can pray near a Decorative Grave giving you a chance to receive a beneficial effect (configurable) or on certain creatures depending on your alignment.
If your alignment is neutral or better, you can use Exorcism to convert a zombie-villager into a villager (or Zombify doing the opposite if your alignment is negative.
If your alignment is +1, you can use Prayer of Protection on a villager (or citizen of Minecolonies) preventing its next death.
If your alignment is +2, you can use Prayer of Empathy to rally a tameable creature.
